    "Bujalance and Moutarde [15] presented a real-time control of the universal robot arm using a pose estimation framework.",
    "In this work, the authors adopted the open pose and human mesh recovery (HMR) frameworks.",
    "Later on, they calculated the inverse kinematics (IK) and forward kinematics (FK) to calculate the joint angles from the given pose key points.",
    "Chamorro et al. [16] proposed a lidar-based gesture recognition system to control the mobile robot for teleoperation.",
    "The authors adopt the long shortterm memory (LSTM) and CNN architecture for pose estimation."
  ],
